title: Temporal Evolution of Land Surface Temperature (LST) in the Study Region: 2003–2023
description: This composite figure illustrates the spatial distribution and increasing trends in Land Surface Temperature (LST) across a coastal region over two decades. Panel (a) depicts LST ranges in 2003 (18.15–30.92°C), showing moderate warming in southern and eastern areas. By 2013 (panel b; 15.23–33.28°C), elevated temperatures expand northward. In 2018 (panel c; 18.43–36.99°C). The 2023 map (panel d; 17.8–37.31°C) reveals widespread extreme temperatures exceeding 30°C, with hotspots nearing 40°C, underscoring long-term thermal escalation.
